    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing system to deliver a linear power band up to an 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and an M Variable Differential Lock for optimal torque distribution. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive valve shim adjustment. The suspension geometry remains precise, benefiting from refreshed bushings and dampers. While the aesthetic reflects honest road use, the mechanical synchronicity and chassis rigidity make this a superlative enthusiast platform.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 31
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used car. Good condition. Well-maintained. Clean title. Minor cosmetic wear. Engine runs strong. No accidents.",
      "price": 34500.0,
